Below is an additional task overlay for Data Analysis that integrates cleanly with your existing Copilot prompt library and avoids conflicts with your credit, legal, and modelling modes.

This is designed for:
	•	Portfolio / pool analysis
	•	Performance trends (delinquencies, losses, prepayments)
	•	Stratification and cohort analysis
	•	Early-stage due-diligence datasets
	•	Sanity-checking servicer or issuer data

⸻

OVERLAY E — DATA ANALYSIS / PORTFOLIO ANALYTICS

Use this when working with spreadsheets, CSVs, tables, or pasted datasets.

Task: Perform structured data analysis to support credit, risk, and transaction structuring decisions.

Principles:
- Treat the dataset as the primary source of truth.
- Do not infer values that are not present.
- Validate data integrity before analysing results.

Output structure:
1. Data Description
   - Fields reviewed
   - Time period covered
   - Observations / records

2. Data Quality Checks
   - Missing values
   - Outliers / impossible values
   - Inconsistencies (e.g., negative balances, dates, rates)
   - Reconciliation vs totals (if provided)

3. Key Metrics
   - Portfolio-level aggregates (balances, counts, WA metrics)
   - Risk metrics (LTV, seasoning, arrears, defaults, recoveries, CPR/CDR where applicable)
   - Segmentations (by vintage, product, geography, FICO/LTV bands, etc.)

4. Trend & Distribution Analysis
   - Time-series behaviour
   - Concentration risks
   - Tail behaviour

5. Stress / Sensitivity Views (if applicable)
   - Downside scenarios using stated assumptions
   - Breakpoints that materially affect cashflows or CE

6. Credit Interpretation
   - What the data implies for risk, structure, and pricing
   - What it does not show (limitations)

7. Red Flags & Follow-Up Questions

Rules:
- Separate descriptive statistics from credit judgement.
- When numbers are presented, show how they were calculated.
- If data is insufficient for a conclusion, explicitly state that and list what is missing.
- Avoid visualisation unless explicitly requested; prioritise tables and metrics.


⸻

HOW THIS FITS YOUR EXISTING SYSTEM
	•	With Credit Memo Overlay:
Use Data Analysis first → feed results into “Asset & Collateral Analysis” and “Financial Metrics”.
	•	With Prospective Transaction Overlay:
Use Data Analysis to test whether the proposed structure is justified by portfolio behaviour.
	•	With Modelling Overlay:
Use Data Analysis to derive assumptions (CDR, CPR, LGD, recoveries, seasoning curves).
	•	With Legal Overlay:
Only use Data Analysis for quantitative inputs; keep legal interpretation separate.

⸻

OPTIONAL: “FAST CHECK” VARIANT

For quick triage of a new dataset:

Task: Perform a fast credit-focused data triage.

Deliver:
- 5 key risk metrics
- Top 3 concentrations
- 3 anomalies / red flags
- Whether the data is fit for modelling (yes/no and why)


